{"key":"processedPost-15321181","value":{"id":15321181,"first":15320387,"last":15339628,"when":1320420136,"utime":"11/04/11 06:22 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>kyoinwyo said:</b><br />i agree with the above, but if you can fan more, by all means do it! mushrooms like 3-4 FAE an hour in nature! maybe still only mist a couple times a day, but fan your FC anytime you think about it!<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Actually, mushrooms in nature do not get fresh air three to four times per hour, they get <b>constant</b> fresh air.<br /><br />I strongly object to the assertion in outdated books that give an 'air exchanges per hour' figure, which totally disregards CO2 levels.&nbsp; Imagine yourself with a plastic bag over your face, where you could only lift it three to four times per hour to take a breath.&nbsp; How long would you survive?<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">A shotgun terrarium</a> does not need to be fanned out, but it's always a good idea to wave the lid over the top whenever you mist, just for added forced air exchange.&nbsp; A shotgun terrarium is designed to provide 24/7 fresh air, just like in nature.&nbsp; This is why it works so well.<br />RR","title":"Re: fanning Shotgun?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}